# =============================================================================
# IPC Hebron VBS — environment template (no secrets committed)
# =============================================================================
# Local: copy to `.env.local` and fill in values. Never commit `.env.local`.
# Prisma CLI commands use `dotenv -e .env.local` (see package.json scripts).
# `npm run db:seed` reads this file from disk (including SEED_* keys) so it still works if a tool only injects some vars into Node.
# =============================================================================

# --- Database (required) ---
# The hostname must be a real host (e.g. localhost or *.postgres.database.azure.com), not the word "HOST".
#
# Docker (`docker compose up` in web/):
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://vbs:vbs_local_dev@localhost:5432/vbs"
#
# Azure PostgreSQL Flexible Server (use your server name + admin user + password; keep sslmode=require):
# Local / dev database name: vbs
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://ADMIN_USER:ADMIN_PASSWORD@your-server.postgres.database.azure.com:5432/vbs?sslmode=require"
# Production (App Service / GitHub prod secrets): use database vbs_production, not vbs.
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://ADMIN_USER:ADMIN_PASSWORD@your-server.postgres.database.azure.com:5432/vbs_production?sslmode=require"
#
# Template (replace every placeholder, especially the host and database name after the port):
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://DB_USER:DB_PASSWORD@your-database-hostname:5432/vbs?sslmode=require"

# --- Auth.js / NextAuth (required) ---
# Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
AUTH_SECRET="replace-with-random-32-bytes-minimum"
# Also signs JWTs for the Expo mobile app (`/api/mobile/v1/*`). Same secret as the web session.
# Local: http://localhost:3000  |  Production: https://your-app.azurewebsites.net
AUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# --- Database seed (npm run db:seed) — SEED_ADMIN_PASSWORD is required (>7 chars) ---
# SEED_ADMIN_EMAIL="admin@yourchurch.org"
# SEED_ADMIN_PASSWORD="your-strong-password-here"

# --- Optional: public registration background images (Azure Blob, recommended in production) ---
# If unset, uploads are written to web/public/uploads (fine locally; often wiped on App Service redeploy).
# Use a dedicated container; enable anonymous blob read or front with CDN so browsers can load the image URL.
# AZURE_STORAGE_CONNECTION_STRING=
# AZURE_STORAGE_CONTAINER=vbs-uploads

# --- Public registration page (optional — shown to families on /register) ---
# NEXT_PUBLIC_VBS_CONTACT_EMAIL=vbs@yourchurch.org
# NEXT_PUBLIC_VBS_CONTACT_PHONE=(555) 123-4567

# --- Staff invite email: Microsoft Graph (optional) ---
# Azure AD app registration: Application permission Microsoft Graph → Mail.Send (admin consent).
# Also used for staff password reset OTP emails on the login screen.
# Client secret from Certificates & secrets. Mailbox = user UPN that sends (e.g. no-reply@yourdomain.org).
# MICROSOFT_GRAPH_TENANT_ID=
# MICROSOFT_GRAPH_CLIENT_ID=
# MICROSOFT_GRAPH_CLIENT_SECRET=
# MICROSOFT_GRAPH_MAILBOX=no-reply@yourdomain.org
# For inbox sync/reply in Incoming Messages, grant app permissions:
# Mail.Read, Mail.Send (admin consent required).
# EMAIL_FROM_DISPLAY_NAME=VBS 2026
# Optional: heading text inside registration emails (defaults to EMAIL_FROM_DISPLAY_NAME).
# REGISTRATION_EMAIL_BRAND=IPC Hebron VBS
#
# If these are unset, invites still work — admins copy the invite link in the UI.

# --- Stripe (optional — public /register card checkout when enabled on a form) ---
# Dashboard: https://dashboard.stripe.com — use test keys locally (sk_test_…, whsec_… from Stripe CLI or webhook endpoint).
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=<paste sk_test_… or sk_live_… from Stripe Dashboard — do not commit real keys>
# Webhook signing secret for POST /api/stripe/webhook (Stripe Dashboard → Developers → Webhooks, or `stripe listen --forward-to localhost:3000/api/stripe/webhook`).
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=<paste whsec_… from Dashboard or stripe listen — do not commit real secrets>
# Optional: defaults to AUTH_URL when set (used for Checkout success/cancel URLs).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# --- Future integrations (placeholders) ---
# SMTP_HOST=
# SMTP_USER=
# SMS_PROVIDER_API_KEY=

# --- SMS (optional): Sent.dm and/or Twilio ---
# If SENT_DM_* is set, Sent.dm is used first. Otherwise Twilio is used when TWILIO_* is set.
# If BOTH are set, a failed Sent.dm send automatically retries once via Twilio unless
# SENT_DM_DISABLE_TWILIO_FALLBACK=true.
#
# --- Sent.dm (https://sent.dm) ---
# Checklist (both required for Sent.dm SMS):
# 1) Dashboard → API keys → create key → SENT_DM_API_KEY
# 2) Dashboard → Templates → create or pick an SMS template approved for UTILITY (or general prose), with ONE
#    placeholder for the full message body, e.g. "{{var_1}}". Do not use AUTHENTICATION / verify-code templates
#    (e.g. sent_Verify_Code_2) for registration SMS — those only allow short numeric codes and return VALIDATION_008.
#    Copy template ID (UUID) → SENT_DM_SMS_TEMPLATE_ID. Inspect a template: npm run sms:sent-template
# 3) Set SENT_DM_TEMPLATE_PARAMETER to match every {{name}} used for the message body. Sent often uses {{var_1}}
#    for a single body placeholder — then use: SENT_DM_TEMPLATE_PARAMETER=var_1
#    (Other examples: message, body, content.)
# 4) If the template has multiple {{variables}}, set SENT_DM_TEMPLATE_PARAMETERS_JSON to a JSON object with the
#    other keys (string/number/boolean values only). The app still fills SENT_DM_TEMPLATE_PARAMETER with the SMS body.
# 5) If the template has NO variables (fixed body in Sent only), set SENT_DM_OMIT_TEMPLATE_PARAMETERS=true (rare for us).
# 6) Optional: Sent dashboard template "name" slug if the API expects it: SENT_DM_SMS_TEMPLATE_NAME=
# Local smoke test (from web/): npm run sms:test-sent -- +15551234567
# This app always sends Sent.dm with "channel": ["sms"] only (per Sent “SMS only” docs). Omitting channel or
# using multi-channel (e.g. whatsapp+sms) can create WhatsApp attempts that fail if WA is not set up.
# SENT_DM_API_KEY=
# SENT_DM_SMS_TEMPLATE_ID=
# SENT_DM_SMS_TEMPLATE_NAME=
# SENT_DM_TEMPLATE_PARAMETER=message
# SENT_DM_TEMPLATE_PARAMETERS_JSON={"brand":"IPC Hebron VBS"}
# SENT_DM_OMIT_TEMPLATE_PARAMETERS=false
# Optional: validate requests without sending (Sent sandbox).
# SENT_DM_SANDBOX=false
# Optional: override API host (default https://api.sent.dm).
# SENT_DM_API_BASE=https://api.sent.dm
#
# Organization-level API keys: if Sent support said to scope requests to a profile, set its UUID:
# SENT_DM_PROFILE_ID=
#
# If the API accepts (202) but the dashboard shows ROUTED → FAILED, that is async carrier/Sent pipeline
# rejection (US A2P/10DLC, template/channel approval, opt-out, balance, KYC). Fetch the real reason:
#   npm run sms:sent-debug -- <message_id_from_activities>
# See https://docs.sent.dm/start/guides/message-status-tracking
# Optional: when both Sent.dm and Twilio are configured, do not fall back to Twilio if Sent.dm fails.
# SENT_DM_DISABLE_TWILIO_FALLBACK=false
#
# --- Twilio (fallback if Sent.dm is not configured) ---
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=ACxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# TWILIO_FROM_PHONE=+15551234567
# Optional brand prefix used in SMS text built by the app.
# REGISTRATION_SMS_BRAND=IPC Hebron VBS

# --- Help / contact email (public pages + email templates) ---
# Global fallback if a season-specific help email is not set in Public registration settings.
# VBS_HELP_EMAIL=vbs@ipchouston.com

# --- Badge printing (optional — planned feature) ---
# Badge layout and fields are configured per season in the admin UI (database), not here.
# Default flow: iPad Safari at /check-in → print to a local/network thermal printer (AirPrint or vendor web print).
# Only set these if you use a server-side print provider or fixed network printer host:
# BADGE_PRINT_PROVIDER=browser
# STAR_WEBPRNT_HOST=192.168.1.50
# ZEBRA_CLOUD_API_KEY=
